### Base64 Image Upload API Tests

### 1. Create a customer first
POST https://localhost:7000/api/Customer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "phone": "123-456-7890"
}

### 2. Upload Base64 image (replace with actual Base64 data)
POST https://localhost:7000/api/Image/upload-base64
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": 1,
  "base64Data": "iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAYAAAAfFcSJAAAADUlEQVR42mNkYPhfDwAChwGA60e6kgAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==",
  "fileName": "test-image.png",
  "contentType": "image/png",
  "description": "Test Base64 image upload"
}

### 3. Get customer images (should include Base64 data)
GET https://localhost:7000/api/Image/customer/1

### 4. Get specific image Base64 data
GET https://localhost:7000/api/Image/base64/1

### 5. Serve image as file (converts Base64 back to bytes)
GET https://localhost:7000/api/Image/serve/1

### 6. Get image count for customer
GET https://localhost:7000/api/Image/count/1

### 7. Upload multiple Base64 images to test 10 image limit
POST https://localhost:7000/api/Image/upload-base64
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": 1,
  "base64Data": "iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAYAAAAfFcSJAAAADUlEQVR42mNkYPhfDwAChwGA60e6kgAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==",
  "fileName": "test-image-2.png",
  "contentType": "image/png",
  "description": "Second test image"
}

### 8. Delete an image
DELETE https://localhost:7000/api/Image/1
